					<a href="http://www.nebosh.org.uk/" target="_new"><p><b>NEBOSH</b></a> National Examination Board in Occupational Safety and Health) is a UK-based independent examination board delivering vocational qualifications in health, safety & environmental practice and management.</p>
					<p>NEBOSH offers a range of qualifications from introductory to professional level. Around 180,000 people worldwide hold a NEBOSH qualification.</p>
					<p>Courses leading to NEBOSH qualifications attract over 30,000 candidates annually and are offered by over 800 Course Providers in 33 countries around the world.</p>
					<p>NEBOSH qualifications are recognised by relevant professional membership bodies including the <a href="http://www.iosh.co.uk/" target="_new">IOSH</a>, <a href="http://www.iirsm.org/" target="_new">IIRSM</a> & <a href="http://www.iema.net/" target="_new">IEMA</a><p>
					<p>NEBOSH maintains Investors in People (IIP) status and is also ISO 9001 certified.  There are three categories of NEBOSH qualification - Award, Certificate and Diploma.<p>
					</td>
                    </tr>	
					<tr>
                    <td width="3%">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="70%"><h4>Accredited Course Providers</h4><p>
					  There are more than 800 organisations worldwide delivering NEBOSH courses which lead to NEBOSH qualifications.</p>
					  <p>NEBOSH Course Providers must be accredited by NEBOSH. The accreditation process ensures Course Providers have procedures and resources in place to deliver training programmes of a standard, required by NEBOSH and to maintain the integrity of the assessment process.</p>
					  <p>Accredited NEBOSH Course Providers not only deliver courses, but also organise exam sittings for candidates.</p>
					  <p>For more information please visit: <a href="http://www.nebosh.org.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.nebosh.org.uk/</a>					  
					 </p></td>
                    </tr>				  
				  <tr>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    <td><h4>About NIST Institute</h4>
						<p>
					  With Great planning and resources, <b>NIST</b> Institute first started its training with <a href="training_IOSH.php#TOP1">IOSH MS </a>on 11th September in the year2008. In the same year, as huge demand for <a href="NEBOSH_IGC.php#TOP1">NEBOSH IGC</a> Certifications started booming, <b>NIST</b> Institute’s Founder has strived rigorously to achieve the NEBOSH accreditation. With lots of dedication, hard work and after completing six successful batches of IOSH MS, NEBOSH courses were first conducted on 20th April 2009.</p>
					  <p>This was one of the biggest leaps for <b>NIST</b> Institute, as this course have helped thousands of individuals to unlock their dreams of getting a lucrative job in the field of Health & Safety, making us, one of the most preferred Institute for Health and Safety services.</p>		<p>Recently <b>NIST</b> Institute completed its 100 batches with NEBOSH and has given certifications to more than 1936 candidates so far, providing a rapid career up gradation to them.</p>
